Sentencas: We demonstrate the Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) nanofiber-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), showing a cathode area-specific resistance (ASR) value of 0.024 Omega cm(2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Nanofiber-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The hollow and porous SSC nanofiber layer, fabricated by electrospinning, is sintered at low temperatures to preserve the high specific surface area for facile oxygen surface exchange reactions.
Titulo: Nanofiber-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The low sintering temperature is enabled by additional SSC powder layer, providing sufficient adhesion between the electrolyte and the nanofiber layer.
Titulo: Nanofiber-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our results can provide a design guideline to fully utilize the nanostructured electrodes by engineering the structural properties of the surface and the interface, and hence high-performance IT-SOFCs can be achieved by structural modification with conventional materials.
Titulo: Nanofiber-based composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
